(685, 'Chandeleur Curlew\'s Toasted Coconut Porter', 'This brown porter base is loaded with tons of roasted malts giving it a plethora of flavors from coffee to chocolate to toffee.  Coconut is added to the boil and to the aging tanks putting a tropical twist on this traditional style.  Curlew is a mostly sand island secluded just far enough away from the main Chandeleur Island chain that it is almost untouched.  There have been many a coconut found on the surfside of this little piece of heaven.', 174, 3, 'https://res.cloudinary.com/ratebeer/image/upload/w_120,c_limit,d_beer_icon_default.png,f_auto/beer_310738.jpg', 310738),
(686, 'Payette Blood Orange Rustler', 'Our compadre Rustler has always had a flair for the theatrical. And this time, it’s a little tropical twist of succulent, juicy, floral blood orange for a smoothness that perfectly balances the dry and mildly bitter hop notes. Variety is the slice of life. Pour yourself a Rustler, with a twist.', 186, 3, 'https://res.cloudinary.com/ratebeer/image/upload/w_120,c_limit,d_beer_icon_default.png,f_auto/beer_435116.jpg', 435116),
(687, 'Warpigs Gose (T)', '', 132, 3, 'https://res.cloudinary.com/ratebeer/image/upload/w_120,c_limit,d_beer_icon_default.png,f_auto/beer_439720.jpg', 439720),
(688, 'Lost+Found R22 APA Fomosaic', 'A modern American Pale Ale with a robust malt profile and full hop hit of tropical fruit and citrus from the Mosaic, Simcoe and Ekuanot hops.\n', 156, 3, 'https://res.cloudinary.com/ratebeer/image/upload/w_120,c_limit,d_beer_icon_default.png,f_auto/beer_592119.jpg', 592119),
(689, 'Sixpoint Sweet Re-Action', 'Original Sweet Action recipe from 2005. Similar to a Belgian Pale Ale, this offering deviates from the\r\nnorm with generous Pacific Northwest hop additions. Also, look for orange peel in the nose and on the palate towards the finish.', 201, 3, 'https://res.cloudinary.com/ratebeer/image/upload/w_120,c_limit,d_beer_icon_default.png,f_auto/beer_92626.jpg', 92626),
